; FFV (ff5c custom build) — Font/Tile Table File
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; Format:   HH=value   (hex byte → display string, no spaces around =)
; Source:   Forked from ffv_menufont_RPGe.tbl; ff5c differences identified
;           via extract_font_tiles.py on ff5c.sfc -> out/ff5c/font/
; Anchor:   B = tile $61  (col 1, row 6 of 16-wide tile grid)  [same as RPGe]
;
; Font graphics: 2bpp SNES, 8x8 pixels/tile
; Tilemap base:  $11F000 (HiROM SNES address)  [same as RPGe]
; Palette:       4 colors sourced near $F827    [same as RPGe]
;
; ff5c vs RPGe differences:
;   - Custom letterforms throughout $20-$93 (visually redesigned, same encoding)
;   - Status icons $3A-$40 redesigned (same game function, new pixel art)
;   - $A6-$A9: 4 new ligatures (were unknown/unused in RPGe)
;   - $B1-$BB: 11 slots repurposed; RPGe used for katakana modifiers, ff5c uses
;              for additional ligatures and/or new icons
;
; Confidence codes: [C] = confirmed via emulator tool
;                   [I] = inferred from tile image analysis
;                   [P] = inherited from ffv_menufont_RPGe.tbl (unchanged)
;                   [?] = uncertain / needs author verification
; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; -- $00-$1F  Control / event codes ------------------------------------------[P]
00=[NUL]
01=[EOL]
02=[Bartz]
03=[03]
04=[04]
05=[05]
06=[06]
07=[07]
08=[08]
